Despite man’s insatiable curiosity, despite his desire to answer life’s most pressing questions both existential and esoteric, the fact remains that even the more earthly facets of reality are themselves rife with uncertainties and unanswered questions — chief among them the depths of our very oceans, and the heavenly bodies scattered across the cosmos.

It should be evident, then, that the untraveled depths of an oceanic planet would be an irresistible enigma for the scientific mind, and in today’s tale we have two: astronauts Agatha Ripley and Leah Weaver, of the United States Space Administration.

The year? 2344. The place? A planet twenty light-years away from the warmth of Earth’s sun. Here, our inquisitors are about to pull on a line of inquiry, and find its hook baited. They are to discover that some answers can only be obtained by taking a dive into uncharted waters, to a place where light itself dare not tread. Because tonight, we’re twenty thousand leagues under the sea, sinking irrecoverably into the abyssal region of the Borderless Confines.

